What you need to know:

Lewandowski's 13th-minute penalty was enough for a win which kept the reigning champions clear of second-placed RB Leipzig, who edged out Union Berlin 1-0 thanks to an Emil Forsberg goalSchalke remained rooted to the foot of the table after slipping to a 2-1 home loss to fellow strugglers CologneSchalke next host Bayern on Sunday having been thrashed 8-0 by the European champions at the Allianz Arena on the opening day of the season